Let $L$ be a $n$-dimensional  Lie algebra over a field $F$. Then the following holds:
\begin{itemize}
\item[(i)] $\langle x, Z^*(L)\rangle$ is nilpotent for all $x\in L$; and
\item[(ii)] if $F$ has characteristic zero, then $Z^*(L)= \nil(L)$.
\end{itemize}

