\label{grado}
Let $L$ be a finite-dimensional Lie algebra over $F_q$. 
\begin{enumerate}[(i)]
    \item Then for every $h\in L\setminus \nil(L)$ we have
\begin{equation}\label{grado2}
  \deg(h) = |\nil_L(h)| - |\nil(L)| - 1.  
\end{equation}
    \item The nilpotent graph of $L$ is never a star graph.
\end{enumerate}

